						<h2>
							Everquest2 & World Of Warcraft signups and little facelift
							Friday, June 18, 2004 - 4:47:19 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I enabled EQ2 and WoW guilds, so they can signup (or pre-signup I guess) their guilds for Guild Wizard.&nbsp; Anyone excited for these games?&nbsp; I am :) ..&nbsp; I am still trying to decide which I like better.. WoW seems like it is going to appeal to me more than EQ2, but who knows.&nbsp; I know I wont have a lot of play-time, so I guess I will play the game that is the friendliest to the casual gamer.&nbsp; Unless a guild or two wants to PL me :) </P>
<P>I also spent some time cleaning up around here.&nbsp; I changed the layout a bit, and changed the navigation, colors and few other cosmetic things.&nbsp;I also created the support page which has links to email and the forums.&nbsp; I also put a Coming Soon for the knowlege base.. i figure if I put that up there, it will give me some motivation to actually make one! </P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Patch
							Thursday, June 17, 2004 - 9:36:11 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I just finished uploading a patch to the forums, and the main system.&nbsp; Here is what I did:</P>
<OL>
<LI>I enabled paging for message views in the forums.&nbsp; When you view a thread that`s longer than 25 messages, it automatically gets put into pages.&nbsp; You can set the page to 25, 50, or 100 posts per page (I will set a default page size in the profile editor in the next patch)</LI>
<LI>The HTML editor will now work in Mozila based browsers as well as IE 5+ browsers</LI>
<LI>The HTML editors will now do a Line Break when you hit Enter, instead of the dumb paragraph tag which causes a double space.&nbsp; Before you had to hit Shift-Enter to get a line break which was pretty dumb..</LI>
<LI>The HTML editor allows you to hit tab and actually get a tab, instead of setting focus to the next available control</LI>
<LI>The Icon for the emotes is now a smiley face in the top left of the toolbar</LI>
<LI>The Quick Reply box will now degrade into a regular text box for non-Internet Explorer users, so it doesnt look retarded in Mozilla.</LI>
<LI>The HTML editor for your News Page and Custom Page Editor will work in Mozilla based browsers as well.&nbsp; It also has an updated image uploader which is a little better than the other one I had in there.. nothing ground breaking but it is a little better</LI>
<LI>I setup the backend Class, Race, and Game classes to scale better for EQ2 and World Of Warcraft.&nbsp; Everquest 2 and WoW will be my main focuses in the next few months, as far as compatibility of features goes.. </LI></OL>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I will probably work some more tonight on the Raid system.&nbsp; I am going to, as long ago promised, allow you now to add raids without having a file.&nbsp; Of course I will still support the raid dumps etc, just I am going to really make the service less dependant on EQ, but keeping all the same EQ specific features.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Voting is next for the forums.. </P>
<P>I will then start on the layout/style overhaul.&nbsp; Thats going to be a big job..&nbsp;</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Forum display names fixed + validators fix
							Tuesday, May 04, 2004 - 10:39:25 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I fixed the issue that was creating some display names in the forum to have a random number appended to the Display Name.&nbsp; Basically, when a user registers, they wont be able to use a Roster account name as a display name.. </P>
<P>I also fixed the validators on the forum registration page, as well as the one on the password change page.&nbsp; The validators in question are the ones that make sure the password and the password confirmation match.. i was checking too soon, which made the validators complain.. and in turn it would confuse the heck out of a lot people.</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Moderators function added to forum
							Thursday, April 29, 2004 - 7:58:57 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>Hot dog! &nbsp;I finally got a few hours to add in the moderator function that I`ve been meaning to code up for the last little while.&nbsp; I am finally getting caught up with work, and have a little time to spare at night to work on guildwizard.&nbsp;Of course this could change just like that if I get busy again.</P>
<P>To add moderators, go into your Manage Forums tab and you will see the Manage Moderators link in the list now.&nbsp; Choose the user and the forum and click the button.&nbsp; To remove the user from the moderator list, click the delete button on the grid underneath which shows all the moderators.&nbsp;</P>
<P>Moderators are NOT admins.&nbsp; They can Delete, Edit, Sticky, Lock threads in the forum(s) they are set to be moderators for.&nbsp; They do not have access to the Manage Forums tab, and may not ban users.</P>
<P>I am really hoping to add in little things here and there over the next few weeks, just the stuff that everyone has been suggesting.&nbsp; Then, after that, I am going to start on a VERY aggressive re-work of the style and layout editor.&nbsp; We are talking a total redevelopment.&nbsp; The whole service + forums will go full XHTML compliant, and allow FULL CSS (Cascading Style Sheet) support.&nbsp; So those users who know css will literally be able to work with their own CSS file.&nbsp; The other 95% of the users are going to work with a much more robust editor than whats there now for style/layout.</P>
<P>I am going to be honest, the above project is really for another project, but heck guildwizard might as well use the same tools :)&nbsp; I wish I could spend quality development time on GuildWizard, but I would have to charge much more to justify it.&nbsp; Keep in mind, with my `real` development projects, I have a dedicated graphic designer, HTML coder, text writer (author) and me as the lead developer for programming.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Anyone playing City of Heros?&nbsp; Send Sharbel on Justice a hello if you are :)</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Hey, they aren`t finished dude.. 
							Saturday, March 27, 2004 - 11:42:26 AM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>Later today I will put a notice on the new forums.. the notice will just be a short message that the forums are in BETA, and are not finished.&nbsp; </P>
<P>I failed to convey this point to a lot of guilds, and I am getting emails asking for this feature and that feature..plus emails complaining that the forums do not have enough features.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Of course they don`t :) they are like 60% done..&nbsp; If the old forums werent having so much trouble, I wouldn`t have even let people use them yet.&nbsp; The plan was to let some people use them, and work on it to get them done in the meantime..&nbsp; Well, the plan didnt exactly work because I have been very busy with my `real` programming work.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Not to worry, I do see me getting some time soon to work on the forums.&nbsp; I just wanted to assure everyone that they aren`t finished..&nbsp; lol they would suck pretty bad if they were :)</P>
						</p>
					
