						<h2>
							Old forums down for restore...
							Tuesday, March 23, 2004 - 5:00:21 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>I am rolling back the old forums to yesterday at around 2pm to try to recover some posts for a few guilds.&nbsp; </P>
<P>I am not sure if its going to be far enough for them, but I figure I will try.&nbsp; This is going to inconvienience a few, and I am sorry for that.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Everyone should switch over to the new beta forums anyway...&nbsp; </P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Old forums days numbered
							Thursday, February 19, 2004 - 1:04:06 AM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>The old forums are on the way out....&nbsp; I don`t have a specific date in mind yet, its basically going to depend on when I get the new forums to a point where I consider the features to be equal, which really isnt that far off.&nbsp; Maybe another couple weeks, as I will probably only get work on the forums on the weekends when i have some spare time.&nbsp; </P>
<P>I know I said that I might allow the old forums to continue to run, but with both running, it`s a big waste of server resources.&nbsp;Now that guilds are really starting to use the new forums, I am seeing that it`s just not going to workout with both forums running.&nbsp; Also, the old forums are starting to act up again with that dumb connection warning.... </P>
<P>I figure I would mention it now, to give those using the old forums a few weeks to let it sink in.... some of the guilds have already started using the new forums.&nbsp; Some are continuing to use them until I turn them off... which is fine.&nbsp; Like I said, I won`t force anyone until the new forums have all the features I want, and they are working 100%.</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Forums: Move threads
							Monday, February 16, 2004 - 11:13:54 PM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>You can now move threads in the new forums by going to the forum manager, and clicking on Move Threads (original eh?).&nbsp; When you select the source forum, a table with all the threads in that forum will populate.. select the thread(s) you want to move, the destination forum and then click the button and it will move&nbsp; them to the new forum.&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>
<P>The forums are getting some good use.&nbsp; Any new guild that signs up is using the new forum, as well as quite a few guilds who have been using guildwizard for a long time.&nbsp; I realize they aren`t polished just yet, but the core functionality is pretty solid so far.&nbsp;</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Forum improvements, login should stick now
							Sunday, February 15, 2004 - 11:40:42 AM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>When you login, it should keep you logged in until you click the logout button, instead of having to login each time.</P>
<P>Forum Features Added:</P>
<UL>
<LI>You can now sort the thread list for a forum by choosing the desired sort in the drop-down-list above the thread list table.&nbsp; The background color of the list is the same background color as your buttons.&nbsp; So if you have a texture for buttons, and didnt set your background color, you should :)</LI>
<LI>You can mark a forum as read by clicking &nbsp;the Mark Forum Read link next to the sort dropdownlist.</LI>
<LI>You can mark all forums read by clicking the Mark All Forums Read link on the forum list</LI>
<LI>The quick reply text-box background color is now transparent (instead of white), and the forecolor (text color) is the same as your Page Text Color that you defined in the color configuration page.</LI></UL>
<P>I think thats it..&nbsp; I might have missed a thing or two.&nbsp; I probably won`t get to the new skins that I wanted to make, I rented Project Gotham Racer II for my Xbox :) Going to be a little busy :)</P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Added new posts icons for forum list
							Saturday, February 14, 2004 - 7:43:45 AM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>When you are logged in and are viewing the forum list, for the new forums, you will now see an icon showing if there are new posts in each forum since your last visit.&nbsp; I will probably add a couple more features over the weekend to the forums..&nbsp; Sorting the threadlist is probably next on the list.</P>
<P>I am also going to try to make up some more skins this weekend, fix some DKP issues, and possibly program a way to add raids without&nbsp;a log file.</P>
<P>Thats my goal anyway :)</P>
						</p>
					
